Pipeline use cases.

preconditions.value: The maintenance schedule indicates a segment of pipeline that is due for "pigging".  The "pig" has been delivered to the launch station.

postconditions.value: The "pig" has traveled to the catcher station and has been extracted. The pipeline segment has been successfully maintained in order to optimize safety and throughput.

description.value: Operations include but are not limited to cleaning and inspecting the pipeline. This is accomplished by inserting the pig into a "pig launcher" (or "launching station"). The launching station is then closed and the pressure-driven flow of the product in the pipeline is used to push the pig along the pipe until it reaches the receiving trap - the "pig catcher" (or "receiving station"). The maintenance procedures are remotely controlled & monitored via the WAN network.

preconditions.value: The pipeline is installed and maintained. A customer has sufficient storage at the outlet station.

postconditions.value: The customer has received the oil/gas at their outlet station. An invoice has been generated for the amount of delivered product.

description.value: Process Customer order for oil/gas by delivering from an appropriate inlet to the customer outlet.  The order processing procedures are remotely controlled & monitored via the WAN network.
